description.narrative: By November 2019, enhanced capacity of staff resulted in improved quality of supplies and the distribution of 88% of Programme goods valued at US$1,154,874.27 (offshore $701,917.18, local $452,957.09) to end users, and the procurement of services and construction works valued at US$2,480,799.66. Some 56% of the supply plan for goods and services was achieved (Supply Plan value $6,458,192.37). | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
